main event: A civilian observed a bright green-white light in the sky over Syosset, Long Island, New York on August 17, 1966 around 9:06 PM. The object was descending rapidly and crossed the sky in about 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as a greenish-white light.
The object was descending rapidly when first observed.
The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes as the object crossed the sky.
The report states the object was not a cataloged satellite.
The Air Force response indicates the object was likely the satellite ECHO I, which was visible in the sky at the time.
